<HL>
   Business Brief -- Lomas Financial Corp.:
   Net Loss of $44.1 Million
   Posted for Fiscal 4th Period
</HL>
<DATE>
09/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10
</SO>
<CO>
   LFC
</CO>
<IN>
DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES, FANNIE MAE, FREDDIE MAC (FIS)
EARNINGS (ERN)
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lomas Financial Corp. reported profit from continuing
operations of $4.9 million, or seven cents a share, for the
fourth quarter ended June 30, compared with a loss from
continuing operations of $282.9 million, or $7.69 a share, in
the year-earlier period.
   The Dallas financial-services and real-estate concern said
losses from discontinued operations of $49 million led to a
net loss of $44.1 million, or $1.25 a share, on revenue of
$69.9 million. In the year-earlier period, losses from
discontinued operations of $20.3 million resulted in a net
loss of $303 million, or $8.26 a share, on revenue of $77.2
million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Lomas has been operating under protection from creditors
under Chapter 11 of the U.S. Bankruptcy Code since last Sept.
24.
   For the year, Lomas reported a net loss of $695.5 million,
or $19.07 a share, including losses from discontinued
operations of $243 million and losses from continuing
operations of $452.4 million, on revenue of $290 million.
   In the year-earlier period, the company reported a net
loss of $298.2 million, or $8.24 a share, including losses
from continuing operations of $311.7 million, a loss from
discontinued operations of $2.2 million and an extraordinary
gain from retirement of debt of $15.7 million, on revenue of
$334 million.
</TEXT>
